# LogQL Query Examples

These examples target application `{{ app.name }}` in namespace `{{ app.namespace }}`.

Labels in Loki depend on the collector configuration. If a query returns no data, inspect available labels in Grafana Explore and adapt the selectors.

## Namespace Logs

```logql
{namespace="{{ app.namespace }}"}
```

## Error Logs

```logql
{namespace="{{ app.namespace }}"} |= "ERROR"
```

## Application Logs By App Label

```logql
{namespace="{{ app.namespace }}", app="{{ app.name }}"}
```

Some collectors normalize Kubernetes labels differently. This alternative may match setups that expose recommended app labels:

```logql
{namespace="{{ app.namespace }}", app_kubernetes_io_name="{{ app.name }}"}
```

## Log Volume Over Five Minutes

```logql
count_over_time({namespace="{{ app.namespace }}"}[5m])
```

## Log Rate Over Five Minutes

```logql
rate({namespace="{{ app.namespace }}"}[5m])
```
